## Summary: Chat Template Handler Structure in llama.cpp

I've thoroughly analyzed the chat template handler structure in the llama.cpp codebase. Here's what you need to know:

---

### **Key Files Containing Chat Template Logic**

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `/common/chat.h` | Header file - core definitions and public API |
| `/common/chat.cpp` | Main implementation (1963 lines) - template handling, auto-parser integration, specialized handlers |
| `/src/llama-chat.h` | Legacy template enum definitions and function signatures |
| `/src/llama-chat.cpp` | Legacy template implementations (920 lines) - hardcoded C++ handlers for known templates (Mistral, Llama 2, etc.) |
| `/common/chat-auto-parser.h` | Structures for auto-parser generation parameters |
| `/common/chat-auto-parser-helpers.h` | Template analysis utilities and diff calculation |
| `/tests/test-chat-template.cpp` | Test framework for chat templates |

---

### **Core Data Structures**

#### **1. Template Registration (`common_chat_template`)**
Located in `common/chat.h` (lines 52-79):
```cpp
struct common_chat_template {
    jinja::program prog;           // Parsed Jinja template
    std::string bos_tok;           // Beginning-of-sequence token
    std::string eos_tok;           // End-of-sequence token
    std::string src;               // Original template source
    chat_template_caps caps;       // Template capabilities (auto-detected)
};
```

The constructor parses the Jinja template and extracts its capabilities automatically.

#### **2. Template Container (`common_chat_templates`)**
Located in `common/chat.cpp` (lines 223-229):
```cpp
struct common_chat_templates {
    bool add_bos;
    bool add_eos;
    bool has_explicit_template;    // Was template user-specified or model-provided?
    std::unique_ptr<common_chat_template> template_default;  // Always set (defaults to chatml)
    std::unique_ptr<common_chat_template> template_tool_use; // Optional tool-specific variant
};
```

#### **3. Input Parameters (`common_chat_templates_inputs`)**
Located in `common/chat.h` (lines 158-175):
